SYMBOLS = (
    ('M', 1000),
    ('CM', 900),
    ('D', 500),
    ('CD', 400),
    ('C', 100),
    ('XC', 90),
    ('L', 50),
    ('XL', 40),
    ('X', 10),
    ('IX', 9),
    ('V', 5),
    ('IV', 4),
    ('I', 1),
)

def solution(input):
    if not input:
        return 0
    for char, value in SYMBOLS:
        if input.startswith(char):
            return value + solution(input[len(char):])
